==English==

=== Noun ===
'''chief'''  (''plural:'' '''[[chiefs]]''')
# A leader or respected elder in a tribe.
#: ''They came to the '''chief''' to resolve their dispute.''
# The head of an organization.
#: ''All firefighters report to the [[fire chief|fire '''chief''']].''
# (''[[heraldry]]'') A horizontal band across the top of a shield.
#: '''1889''': When the '''Chief''' is Charged with any figure, in blazon it is said to be "''On a '''Chief'''''". &mdash; Charles Norton Elvin, ''A Dictionary of Heraldry''

=== Adjective ===
'''chief'''
# Primary.
#: ''Negligence was the '''chief''' cause of the disaster.''

